  h2 Karla and Co.
  video(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/bb2.mp4" class="img__50" playsinline="playsinline" loop controls)
  h2 Bigger brands
  p Bigger brands are getting in on the action as well. Let’s look at a few more examples:
  p At the start of this year's football season BT Sport began uploading!{' '}
    a(href="https://giphy.com/BTSport/") GIF's
    |!{' '}of all Premier League players (embedding their own logo in the top right).
  p Now if you search for any player (e.g. - “De Gea”) you're reminded that BT have the rights to Premier League matches:
  video(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/bb1.mp4" class="img__70" playsinline="playsinline" loop controls)
  h2 Who's this for?
  p Consumer brands and influencers targeting a young, hip audience are the ones jumping on this strategy (e.g.!{' '}
    a(href="https://giphy.com/prettylittlething") Pretty Little Thing
    | ,!{' '}
    a(href="https://giphy.com/angrybirds") Angry Birds
    | ,!{' '}
    a(href="https://giphy.com/liljon") Lil Jon
    |!{' '}etc .) But that’s also where the competition is at.
  p If you’re an “influencer” in the web development space!{' '}
    span.bold literally no one is doing this
    | . Sooner or later youngsters are going to start sending “I ❤️Javascript” GIF’s to each other and if you hit those keywords first you’ll see some nice returns.
  p I was planning on doing this myself. I had a made a bunch of marketing themed GIF’s with the Marketing Examples URL embedded but I was told by Giphy that “brand channels” must produce original content. So I turned the idea into Startup GIF’s instead.
  h2 Stickers or GIF's
  p One thing worth thinking about is whether to create!{' '}
    a(href="") GIF’s
    |!{' '}or!{' '}
    a(href="") stickers
    | .
  p GIF's have solid backgrounds, stickers have transparent backgrounds. And Giphy has seperate API's for each which different apps plug into:
  p.list.list__top • Facebook - GIF API
  p.list • Whats App - GIF API
  p.list • Instagram - Sticker API
  p.list.list__bottom • TikTok - Sticker API
  p Your decision to create stickers or GIF’s or stickers depends on what platform your audience hangs out on. For example Pretty Little audience exists on Instagram so
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/giphy2.jpg" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__90
  p.list.list__top • Pretty Little Thing - Audience Instagrma
  p.list.list__bottom • Facebook - GIF API
  h2 Summary
  p To summarise the steps to make this work:

  1. Create GIF’s relevant to what your target audience might search for
2. Tag them with relevant keywords
3. Remember to add logo / url back to your product
3. Once you have 5 GIF’s you can apply for a brand account
4. Once you have have a brand account your GIF’s go public on Giphy’s API
